nfo_sec1       = \n| blank4_name_sec1       = \n| blank4_info_sec1       = \n| blank5_name_sec1       = \n| blank5_info_sec1       = \n| blank6_name_sec1       = \n| blank6_info_sec1       = \n| blank7_name_sec1       = \n| blank7_info_sec1       = \n| blank1_name_sec2       = Major religions\n| blank1_info_sec2       = \n| blank2_name_sec2       = Feast date\n| blank2_info_sec2       = \n| blank3_name_sec2       = Catholic diocese\n| blank3_info_sec2       =\n| blank4_name_sec2       = Patron saint \n| blank4_info_sec2       = \n| blank5_name_sec2       = \n| blank5_info_sec2       = \n| blank6_name_sec2       = \n| blank6_info_sec2       = \n| blank7_name_sec2       = \n| blank7_info_sec2       =\n| short_description      =\n| footnotes              =\n}}\n\n'''{{PH wikidata|name}}''', officially the '''{{PH wikidata|official_name}}''',  is a {{PH wikidata|income_class_ordinal}} [[{{PH wikidata|settlement_text}} of the Philippines|{{PH wikidata|settlement_text}}]] in the [[Philippine Province|province]] of {{PH wikidata|province}}, {{PH wikidata|country}}. According to the {{PH wikidata|population_as_of}}, it has a population of {{PH wikidata|population_total}} people.{{PH census|current}}\n\nIt is situated on the north shore of [[Lake Mainit]] in the north-eastern part of [[Mindanao]]. The word \"''mainit''\" literally means \"hot\".\n\n==Barangays==\nMainit is politically subdivided into 21 [[barangay]]s. In 1956, the sitios of Magpayang and Siana were elevated as barrios.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lawph.com/statutes/ra1543.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120711105628/http://lawph.com/statutes/ra1543.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-11 |title=An Act Converting into Barrios Certain Sitios in the Province of Surigao, and Dividing the Barrio of Macalaya into Two Barrios, Municipality of Placer, in the Same Province |publisher=LawPH.com |accessdate=2011-04-12 }}</ref>\n\n{{div col}}\n* Binga  \n* Bobona-on \n* Cantugas \n* Dayano \n* Mabini \n* Magpayang \n* Magsaysay ([[Poblacion]]) \n* Mansayao \n* Marayag \n* Matin-ao \n* Paco \n* Quezon ([[Poblacion]]) \n* Roxas \n* San Francisco \n* San Isidro \n* San Jose \n* Siana \n* Silop \n* Tagbuyawan \n* Tapi-an \n* Tolingon \n{{div col end}}\n\n==History==\nThe first inhabitants of Mainit settled near Lake Mainit in what is now barangay San Isidro. It was believed that the constant harassment of pirates forced the original settlers to move to the present town site.\n\nMainit was made into a barrio in 1904 under the Municipality of Placer. In 1906, it became a Municipality of Agusan Province but after six months, Mainit was returned to the Province of Surigao del Norte and its status was reverted to being a barangay of Placer. Mainit was finally made into a municipality in Jan. 1, 1931 by virtue of Executive Order 290 dated December 27, 1930,<ref>http://mainithistory.wordpress.com/2010/10/01/hello-world/ Executive Order 290 dated December 27, 1930</ref> signed by Governor-General Dwight F. Davis.\n\nTwo of Mainit's barangays were made into full-fledged municipalities: [[Tubod, Surigao del Norte|Tubod]] in 1958 and [[Alegria, Surigao del Norte|Alegria]] in 1968. and Mainit the mainit has many Barangays Magsaysay, Quezon,Mansayao and others\n\nMainit got its name from the hot sulfuric spring which flows to the river the \u201cMapaso Hot Spring\u201d. Mapaso literally is \u201chot\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://mainitsurigao.wordpress.com/2009/12/21/history-vision-mission|title= History, Vision and Mission|accessdate= 2010-09-15|author= Municipality of Mainit|date= 2009-12-21}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Philippine Census\n| cols = 2\n| align= none\n| title= Population census of Mainit\n| 1903 = 1588\n| 1918 = \n| 1939 = 13951\n| 1948 = 17681\n| 1960 = 18542\n| 1970 = 14759\n| 1975 = 17064\n| 1980 = 18078\n| 1990 = 21505\n| 1995 = 21780\n| 2000 = 23417\n| 2007 = 23952\n| 2010 = 25596\n| 2015 = 26741\n| 2020 =\n| 2025 =\n| 2030 =\n| footnote= Source: [[Philippine Statistics Authority]]{{PH census|2015}}{{PH census|2010}}{{PH census|2007}}{{LWUA population data}} \n}}\n\nThe [[Surigaonon language]] is the common local language, while [[Cebuano language|Cebuano]], [[Filipino language|Filipino]], and [[English Language|English]] are also spoken.\n\n==Climate==\n{{Weather box\n| location     = Mainit, Surigao del Norte\n| width        = auto\n| metric first = Yes\n| single line  = Yes\n| Jan high C = 27\n| Jan low C  = 23\n| Feb high C = 27\n| Feb low C  = 23\n| Mar high C = 28\n| Mar low C  = 23\n| Apr high C = 29\n| Apr low C  = 23\n| May high C = 30\n| May low C  = 24\n| Jun high C = 29\n| Jun low C  = 25\n| Jul high C = 29\n| Jul low C  = 24\n| Aug high C = 29\n| Aug low C  = 25\n| Sep high C = 29\n| Sep low C  = 24\n| Oct high C = 29\n| Oct low C  = 24\n| Nov high C = 28\n| Nov low C  = 24\n| Dec high C = 28\n| Dec low C  = 24\n| Jan precipitation mm = 210\n| Feb precipitation mm = 161\n| Mar precipitation mm = 123\n| Apr precipitation mm = 85\n| May precipitation mm = 148\n| Jun precipitation mm = 186\n| Jul precipitation mm = 164\n| Aug precipitation mm = 157\n| Sep precipitation mm = 141\n| Oct precipitation mm = 190\n| Nov precipitation mm = 223\n| Dec precipitation mm = 200\n| Jan rain days        = 21.0\n| Feb rain days        = 16.8\n| Mar rain days        = 18.5\n| Apr rain days        = 18.2\n| May rain days        = 24.9\n| Jun rain days        = 27.7\n| Jul rain days        = 28.4\n| Aug rain days        = 27.0\n| Sep rain days        = 26.1\n| Oct rain days        = 27.6\n| Nov rain days        = 24.6\n| Dec rain days        = 22.0\n| source 1 = Meteoblue <ref name=\"met_norms\">\n{{cite web \n| url = https://www.meteoblue.com/en/weather/historyclimate/climatemodelled/mainit_philippines_1703518\n| title =  Mainit: Average Temperatures and Rainfall\n| publisher = Meteoblue\n| accessdate = 20 November 2019 }}</ref>\n| date = 20 November 2019 \n}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Lake Mainit Development Alliance]]\n\n==Refere